# High altitude chocolate chip muffins

## Ingredients
* 1 3/4 cups all-purpose flour
* 1 tbsp cornstarch
* 1/2 cup sugar
* 1/4 tsp salt
* 1 tsp baking soda
* 2 large eggs, room temperature
* 1 tbsp white vinegar
* 1 cup - 1 tbsp whole milk, room temperature
* 1/2 cup unsalted butter
* 2 tsp vanilla extract
* 3/4 cup mini chocolate chips

## Steps
1. Preheat the oven to 400.
1. Put the 1 tbsp white vinegar into a 1 cup measuring cup. Fill the measuring cup up the rest of the way with milk. Let sit while preparing the rest of the stuff.
1. Melt the butter. Let sit while preparing the rest of the stuff so it cools a little before needing to be used.
1. Sift together the flour, cornstarch, sugar, salt, and baking soda.
1. Whisk together the eggs, milk + vinegar mixture, butter, and vanilla.
1. Combine the wet and dry ingredients, and whisk until just combined.
1. Stir in the chocolate chips.
1. Put the batter into greased muffin tins, filling almost all the way full.
1. Put into the oven and immediately drop the temp to 375.
1. Bake about 9 minutes for mini muffins, or about 18 for normal-sized muffins.

## Notes
* The vinegar thing is a buttermilk substitute.

